cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the economic and regulatory aspects of network neutrality, which are closely related to computer networks and the Internet. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses game theory and optimization techniques to model the interactions between different stakeholders, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses security and privacy concerns related to network neutrality, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. Finally, the paper uses queueing theory to model delays in content delivery, which could also make it relevant to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) category.
